\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf6 Plot/Action:<!$Scr_Ps::3><$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 Beginning:}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 <$Scr_Cs::2> The scene starts with Patti observing Evan and Sarah in the parking lot as he is giving her the doll, and they are being affectionate, giggling, and having a good time. Every time Evan kisses Sarah, it feels like a punch in the gut to Patti. We want the reader to experience, through deeper POV and internal dialogue, how Patti is feeling as she is watching Evan with a new woman.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 Middle: <!$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li878\fi-144\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls1\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Roxanne sees Patti watching Evan and Sarah and makes derogatory comments about Sarah.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Guido is warming up, playing catch nearby. Roxanne calls them over to get the scoop on Sarah.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Guido informs them he hasn't even met her yet. He has little to tell them except that Evan seems crazy about this chick.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Roxanne was surprised that Patti didn't see Evan's relationship status change on Facebook.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Adding shock to Patti's system is that she had no idea Evan has a new girlfriend or that she would be attending the game.}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li346\fi14\sb60\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf7 <$Scr_Ps::4>End: <!$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li878\fi-144\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls2\ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Evan introduces Sarah to his group of friends watching from the bleachers and Guido. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Conflicted between wanting to support Evan and welcome his girlfriend into their inner circle and feeling like a jilted ex-girlfriend, Patti forces a silent smile after the introduction. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 Immediately after the introduction, the team\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s coach calls Evan and Guido in for the start of the game. }
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf8 This is where the scene ends.}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\sb180\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Ps::5>Objectives/Goals:}
\par\pard\plain \tx235\tx720\li576\fi-486\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch \ls3\ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 The primary objective of the scene is to help readers understand Evan's romantic relationships before Sarah. Please review Patti and Evan's profiles to understand Evan's exclusive and monogamous but casual college relationships before Sarah.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 Through Patti's eyes, we see that Sarah differs from his past relationships. And at this point in the story, no one can be sure if the relationship will last and why Evan would choose Sarah over Patti. Patti is every bit as beautiful as Sarah and far more compatible.}
\par\plain \ilvl0{\listtext	\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \uc0\u8226 	}{\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf1 It is crucial to understand Patti's conflict in this scene. In the previous school year, Patti was well aware of Evan's unusual monogamous but casual relationship history. He never deceived her or called her his girlfriend. They were good friends before they started sleeping together. However, somewhere along the line, Patti developed strong feelings for Evan and began to feel like a girlfriend. She lasted twice as long as any other girl Evan was with, and Evan even introduced Patti to his sister \endash  something he had never done before. However, when the school year ended, and Patti went back home for summer break, the intimate aspect of the relationship ended. When the current school year started, Evan treated her as a good friend, as though the intimate part of the relationship had never happened. She thought he would come around and be with her again, and the next thing you know, he has a girlfriend.}
